{
  "stem": "17625.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the other ones were looking.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were looking, and they gave us a-- a- a plate.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You know what it means?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And from there, they took us on a-- on a-- on a-- on a-- a truck.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They took us out from there-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and to a-- to another-- [LAUGHS] to-- to another camp-- to another thing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And there again, they en-loused us again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You know what it means, en-louse, yeah?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Same thing what was in Birkenau-- they took us to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They en-loused us again, and they brought us in to block 11 in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I didn't know what it is-- what block 11 is.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They took us to block 11.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Over there, they let us-- let us in with the-- with SS man in front at the door.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You know what I mean?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "You couldn't-- in the other-- the other blocks, it was open.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But this was closed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] coming in there, they took us to the basement.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And over there in the basement was already a-- a group.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we joined them-- coffee, whatever. 5 o'clock in the morning, next morning, they woke us up.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they walked us out in the morning-- dark, no appeal-- no appell, no nothing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They walked us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A guard walk-- two guards or one guard, walked us out of the camp, from the [NON-ENGLISH], where we came in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And a short walk, we saw a building standing there with a-- with-- with a-- with a wood-- with a fence, a-- a wooden fence or a hard fence.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they opened up the gate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they-- and they brought us in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Over there, we met [SIGHS] a young guy, a-- a-- a Polack.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
